{"title_page": "Verband Christlicher Pfadfinderinnen und Pfadfinder", "text_new": "{{refimprove|date=April 2018}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2014}}\n{{infobox WorldScouting\n|type=organization\n|image=Verband Christlicher Pfadfinderinnen und Pfadfinder (VCP) Logo (Lilie).svg\n|name2=Association of Christian Scouts and Guides\n|name=Verband Christlicher Pfadfinderinnen und Pfadfinder\n|headquarters=\n|location=[[Kassel]]\n|country=Germany\n|f-date={{start date|1973}}\n|founder=\n|award-for=\n|members=47,000\n|chiefscouttitle=Bundesvorstand\n|chiefscout=Oliver Mahn, Neals Nowitzki, Natascha Sonnenberg\n|website=http://www.vcp.de\n}}\n\nThe '''Verband Christlicher Pfadfinderinnen und Pfadfinder''' (roughly: ''Association of Christian Guides and Scouts'', VCP) is a [[Germany|German]] [[Protestant]] coed [[Scouting]] and [[Girl Guides|Guiding]] association. According to the VCP, the organization has about 47,000 members.\n\nIt is a member of the [[Ring deutscher Pfadfinderverb\u00e4nde]] (''Federation of German Scouting Associations'', RdP), which in turn is a member of the [[World Organization of the Scout Movement]] (WOSM), and a member of the [[Ring Deutscher Pfadfinderinnenverb\u00e4nde]] (''Federation of German Guiding Associations'', RDP), which in turn is a member of the [[World Association of Girl Guides and Girl Scouts]] (WAGGGS). <ref>{{cite web|title=Unser Verband|url=http://www.vcp.de/wer-wir-sind/unser-verband/|publisher=Verband Christlicher Pfadfinderinnen und Pfadfinder|accessdate=26 April 2018}}</ref>\n\n== History ==\nThe association was formed in 1973 through the merger of three Protestant associations:\n* ''Bund Christlicher Pfadfinderinnen'' (founded in 1922; only in [[Bavaria]]; girls only)\n* ''Christliche Pfadfinderschaft Deutschlands'' (first groups in 1910, founded in 1921; boys only until 1969)\n* ''Evangelischer M\u00e4dchen-Pfadfinderbund'' (founded in 1926; not in Bavaria; girls only)\n\nIn 1976, some traditional Scouting groups left and formed a separate association, using the former name ''Christliche Pfadfinderschaft Deutschlands'' again.<ref>{{cite web|title=Geschichte|url=http://www.c-p-d.info/unser-bund/geschichte/|publisher=Christliche Pfadfinderschaft Deutschlands|accessdate=26 April 2018|language=german}}</ref>\n\nTwo years later, the VCP held his first national [[jamboree (Scouting)|jamboree]]. Since then, roughly every four years a national jamboree has taken place:\n* 1978 - [[Kirchberg, Rhein-Hunsr\u00fcck|Kirchberg]], near [[Koblenz]]\n* 1984 - [[Eschwege]]\n* 1988 - [[Ruhpolding]]\n* 1992 - [[Ferschweiler Plateau]], near [[Trier]]\n* 1998 - [[Rheinsberg]] in [[Brandenburg]]\n* 2002 - [[Rehau]], near [[Nuremberg]]\n* 2006 - Gro\u00dfzerlang, near [[Rheinsberg]] in [[Brandenburg]]\n* 2010 - [[Wolfsburg]]\n* 2014 - Schachen, near [[M\u00fcnsingen,_Germany|M\u00fcnsingen]] in  [[Baden-Wurttemberg]]\n* 2017 - [[Wittenberg]]\n\nIn 1990, after the [[fall of the Berlin Wall]], the first groups of Protestant Scouts and Guides were formed in the still existent [[East Germany|German Democratic Republic]]. Today, the VCP is present in all [[States of Germany|Federal States]] of Germany.<ref>{{cite web|title=Landesb\u00fcros|url=http://www.vcp.de/kontakt/landesbueros/|publisher=Verband Christlicher Pfadfinderinnen und Pfadfinder|accessdate=24 April 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Program ==\nThe association is divided in three age-groups:\n* Kinderstufe - [[Cub Scouts]] (ages 7 to 10)\n* Pfadfinderstufe - Scouts (ages 10 to 15)\n**Jungpfadfinderinnen and Jungpfadfinder (ages 10 to 13)\n**Pfadfinderinnen and Pfadfinder (ages 13 to 16)\n* Roverstufe - [[Rover Scouts]] (ages 16 to 20)\n\nThe age-groups can be identified by their scarfs. Cubs wear scarfs with orange stripes, Jungpfadfinder with light green stripes, Pfadfinder scarfs with dark green stripes and Ranger/Rover scarfes with bordeaux-red stripes. \n\nThere is also a special branch for adults in Scouting, the ''Erwachsenenarbeit'', which aims at all members older than 21 years including leaders and non-leaders. They wear scarfs with purple stripes<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vcp.de/das-ist-pfadfinden-im-vcp/grundsaetze/|title=VCP - Grunds\u00e4tze|website=www.vcp.de|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref>. \n\nLike most German Scout associations, the VCP emphasizes on youth leadership. Most patrol leaders start at 16 and most leaders up to district level are younger than 25.\n\n=== Promise ===\nThe VCP has no common [[Scout Promise]]. Its constitution proposes the following text, but other wordings are possible:\n:Im Vertrauen auf Gottes Hilfe\n:will ich christliche Pfadfinderin/christlicher Pfadfinder sein\n:und nach unseren Regeln mit euch leben.\n\n:''Trusting on the help of God''\n:''I want to be a Christian Scout/Christian Guide''\n:''and to live with you according to our rules.''\n\n=== Rules ===\nThe association has no common [[Scout Law]]. It uses Scout rules, which should be formulated individually by each group. The constitution proposes a number of points, which should go into these rules. Despite this, many subdivisions of the association use a common Scout Law.\n\n== Scout centres ==\nThe VCP runs two national Scout centres:\n* [[Rieneck Castle]] in [[Lower Franconia]], near [[W\u00fcrzburg]]\n* ''VCP-Bundeszeltplatz'' (National Campground of the VCP) in Gro\u00dfzerlang near [[Rheinsberg]] in [[Brandenburg]]\nas well as a number of regional Scout centres mostly maintained by subnational divisions of the association.\n\nRieneck Castle was leased by the ''Christliche Pfadfinderschaft Deutschlands'' in 1959 and bought in 1967. It is mainly used for training courses on national level, and the annual International Creative Workshop (IMWe). The VCP-Bundeszeltplatz was bought in 1997 and hosts camps from group to national level.\n\n== International Creative Workshop ==\nThe International Creative Workshop<ref name=\"IMWe Norway\">{{cite web |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190425144847/https://speiding.no/speiderprogram/speiderbasen/international-creative-workshop-imwe |url=https://speiding.no/speiderprogram/speiderbasen/international-creative-workshop-imwe |language=English, Norwegian |title=International Creative Workshop (IMWe) |date=28 March 2008 |first=Jostein |last=S\u00f8vik |archivedate=25 April 2019 |accessdate=25 April 2019 |url-status=live |website=[[Speiding.no]]}}</ref> ([[German language|German]]: ''Internationale Musische Werkstatt'' (IMWe))<ref name=\"eventsi\">{{cite web |url-status=live |title=IMWe 2018 - International Creative Workshop for Scouts |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190425144731/https://www.evensi.de/imwe-2018-international-creative-workshop-scouts-burg-rieneck-guide-scout-castle/208642623 |url=https://www.evensi.de/imwe-2018-international-creative-workshop-scouts-burg-rieneck-guide-scout-castle/208642623 |date=3 April 2018 |archivedate=25 April 2019 |accessdate=25 April 2019 |website=eventsi.de}}</ref> is an annual [[Scouting]] and [[Girl Guides|Guiding]] event run by the VCP.<ref name=\"Pfadi in Deutschland\">{{cite book |title=Die Pfadfinder in Deutschland 1909 - 2009 |trans-title=Scouting in Germany 1909 - 2009 |publisher=Novum Publishing |year=2011 |ISBN=978-3-99003-246-6 |first=Piet |last=Strunk |page=255 |language=German}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190425150605/https://www.der-kirchenkreis.de/de/aktuell/nachrichten/nachricht/article/bundesverdienstorden-fuer-bocholter-ehrenamt/ |date=12 October 2013 |url=https://www.der-kirchenkreis.de/de/aktuell/nachrichten/nachricht/article/bundesverdienstorden-fuer-bocholter-ehrenamt/ |title=Bundesverdienstorden f\u00fcr Bocholter Ehrenamt |trans-title=Federal Merit Order for Bocholt volunteer |url-status=live |language=German |archivedate=25 April 2019 |accessdate=25 April 2019 |publisher=[[Evangelical Church of Westphalia|Kirchenkreis Steinfurt-Coesfeld-Borken Evangelical Church]]}}</ref> It usually takes place at [[Rieneck Castle]].<ref name=\"IMWe Norway\"/> As a [[Wood Badge]] training event,<ref name=\"Pfadi in Deutschland\"/> the aim of IMWe is to give leaders of Guide and Scout groups the opportunity to explore their creative talents in a relaxed setting.<ref name=\"IMWe Norway\"/> IMWe is prepared on behalf of the VCP by an international group of scouts<ref name=\"IMWe Iceland\">{{cite web |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140720054132/http://skatamal.is/imwe |url=http://skatamal.is/imwe |website=[[skatamal.is]] |url-status=live |title=Vi\u00f0 beislum sk\u00f6punarkraftinn og n\u00fdtum \u00ed starfi\u00f0 |language=Icelandic |trans-title=We harness creativity and use it for the job |date=29 April 2014 |archivedate=20 July 2014 |accessdate=25 April 2019}}</ref> who meet several times a year to organize the workshop, which is held around [[Easter]].<ref name=\"IMWe Norway\"/> The workshop lasts for 8 or 9 days, with a [[Scout method#Symbolic framework|symbolic framework]] or theme.<ref name=\"IMWe Norway\"/> Participants have to be aged 17 years or older.<ref name=\"eventsi\"/><ref name=\"IMWe Norway\"/><ref>{{cite web |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190425144225/https://www.scout.ch/de/pfadialltag/internationales/lager/international-lager |url=https://www.scout.ch/de/pfadialltag/internationales/lager/international-lager |url-status=live |archivedate=25 April 2019 |accessdate=25 April 2019 |title=IMWE |website=[[Scout.ch]]}}</ref> IMWe has been represented at international Scouting events such as [[EuroJam 2005]]<ref>{{cite web |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160831151142/http://www.theblackmagic.de/54.html |url=http://www.theblackmagic.de/54.html |language=German |title=Buehne |trans-title=Stage |archivedate=31 August 2016 |publisher=[[Ring deutscher Pfadfinderverb\u00e4nde|German Contingent to the 2011 World Scout Jamboree]] |accessdate=25 April 2019}}</ref> and [[World Scout Moot]] in 2015.<ref name=\"IMWe Moot\">{{cite report |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180613185150/http://worldscoutmoot.is/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/Moot-Handbook-English.pdf |url-status=live |title=Moot Handbook |publisher=[[The Scout Association|UK Contingent to the 2017 World Scout Moot]] |archivedate=13 June 2018 |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180613185150/http://worldscoutmoot.is/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/Moot-Handbook-English.pdf#page=21 |page=21 |accessdate=25 April 2019}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Scouting in Germany]]\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Official website}}\n* [http://www.imwe.net IMWe homepage]\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Scouting and Guiding in Germany]]\n[[Category:World Association of Girl Guides and Girl Scouts member organizations]]\n[[Category:World Organization of the Scout Movement member organizations]]\n[[Category:Youth organizations established in 1973]]\n", "text_old": "{{refimprove|date=April 2018}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2014}}\n{{infobox WorldScouting\n|type=organization\n|image=Verband Christlicher Pfadfinderinnen und Pfadfinder (VCP) Logo (Lilie).svg\n|name2=Association of Christian Scouts and Guides\n|name=Verband Christlicher Pfadfinderinnen und Pfadfinder\n|headquarters=\n|location=[[Kassel]]\n|country=Germany\n|f-date={{start date|1973}}\n|founder=\n|award-for=\n|members=47,000\n|chiefscouttitle=Bundesvorstand\n|chiefscout=Oliver Mahn, Neals Nowitzki, Natascha Sonnenberg\n|website=http://www.vcp.de\n}}\n\nThe '''Verband Christlicher Pfadfinderinnen und Pfadfinder''' (roughly: ''Association of Christian Guides and Scouts'', VCP) is a [[Germany|German]] [[Protestant]] coed [[Scouting]] and [[Girl Guides|Guiding]] association. According to the VCP, the organization has about 47,000 members.\n\nIt is a member of the [[Ring deutscher Pfadfinderverb\u00e4nde]] (''Federation of German Scouting Associations'', RdP), which in turn is a member of the [[World Organization of the Scout Movement]] (WOSM), and a member of the [[Ring Deutscher Pfadfinderinnenverb\u00e4nde]] (''Federation of German Guiding Associations'', RDP), which in turn is a member of the [[World Association of Girl Guides and Girl Scouts]] (WAGGGS). <ref>{{cite web|title=Unser Verband|url=http://www.vcp.de/wer-wir-sind/unser-verband/|publisher=Verband Christlicher Pfadfinderinnen und Pfadfinder|accessdate=26 April 2018}}</ref>\n\n== History ==\nThe association was formed in 1973 through the merger of three Protestant associations:\n* ''Bund Christlicher Pfadfinderinnen'' (founded in 1922; only in [[Bavaria]]; girls only)\n* ''Christliche Pfadfinderschaft Deutschlands'' (first groups in 1910, founded in 1921; boys only until 1969)\n* ''Evangelischer M\u00e4dchen-Pfadfinderbund'' (founded in 1926; not in Bavaria; girls only)\n\nIn 1976, some traditional Scouting groups left and formed a separate association, using the former name ''Christliche Pfadfinderschaft Deutschlands'' again.<ref>{{cite web|title=Geschichte|url=http://www.c-p-d.info/unser-bund/geschichte/|publisher=Christliche Pfadfinderschaft Deutschlands|accessdate=26 April 2018|language=german}}</ref>\n\nTwo years later, the VCP held his first national [[jamboree (Scouting)|jamboree]]. Since then, roughly every four years a national jamboree has taken place:\n* 1978 - [[Kirchberg, Rhein-Hunsr\u00fcck|Kirchberg]], near [[Koblenz]]\n* 1984 - [[Eschwege]]\n* 1988 - [[Ruhpolding]]\n* 1992 - [[Ferschweiler Plateau]], near [[Trier]]\n* 1998 - [[Rheinsberg]] in [[Brandenburg]]\n* 2002 - [[Rehau]], near [[Nuremberg]]\n* 2006 - Gro\u00dfzerlang, near [[Rheinsberg]] in [[Brandenburg]]\n* 2010 - [[Wolfsburg]]\n* 2014 - Schachen, near [[M\u00fcnsingen,_Germany|M\u00fcnsingen]] in  [[Baden-Wurttemberg]]\n* 2017 - [[Wittenberg]]\n\nIn 1990, after the [[fall of the Berlin Wall]], the first groups of Protestant Scouts and Guides were formed in the still existent [[East Germany|German Democratic Republic]]. Today, the VCP is present in all [[States of Germany|Federal States]] of Germany.<ref>{{cite web|title=Landesb\u00fcros|url=http://www.vcp.de/kontakt/landesbueros/|publisher=Verband Christlicher Pfadfinderinnen und Pfadfinder|accessdate=24 April 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Program ==\nThe association is divided in three age-groups:\n* Kinderstufe - [[Cub Scouts]] (ages 7 to 10)\n* Pfadfinderstufe - Scouts (ages 10 to 15)\n**Jungpfadfinderinnen and Jungpfadfinder (ages 10 to 13)\n**Pfadfinderinnen and Pfadfinder (ages 13 to 16)\n* Roverstufe - [[Rover Scouts]] (ages 16 to 20)\n\nThe age-groups can be identified by their scarfs. Cubs wear scarfs with orange stripes, Jungpfadfinder with light green stripes, Pfadfinder scarfs with dark green stripes and Ranger/Rover scarfes with bordeaux-red stripes. \n\nThere is also a special branch for adults in Scouting, the ''Erwachsenenarbeit'', which aims at all members older than 21 years including leaders and non-leaders. They wear scarfs with purple stripes<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vcp.de/das-ist-pfadfinden-im-vcp/grundsaetze/|title=VCP -\u00a0Grunds\u00e4tze|website=www.vcp.de|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref>. \n\nLike most German Scout associations, the VCP emphasizes on youth leadership. Most patrol leaders start at 16 and most leaders up to district level are younger than 25.\n\n=== Promise ===\nThe VCP has no common [[Scout Promise]]. Its constitution proposes the following text, but other wordings are possible:\n:Im Vertrauen auf Gottes Hilfe\n:will ich christliche Pfadfinderin/christlicher Pfadfinder sein\n:und nach unseren Regeln mit euch leben.\n\n:''Trusting on the help of God''\n:''I want to be a Christian Scout/Christian Guide''\n:''and to live with you according to our rules.''\n\n=== Rules ===\nThe association has no common [[Scout Law]]. It uses Scout rules, which should be formulated individually by each group. The constitution proposes a number of points, which should go into these rules. Despite this, many subdivisions of the association use a common Scout Law.\n\n== Scout centres ==\nThe VCP runs two national Scout centres:\n* [[Rieneck Castle]] in [[Lower Franconia]], near [[W\u00fcrzburg]]\n* ''VCP-Bundeszeltplatz'' (National Campground of the VCP) in Gro\u00dfzerlang near [[Rheinsberg]] in [[Brandenburg]]\nas well as a number of regional Scout centres mostly maintained by subnational divisions of the association.\n\nRieneck Castle was leased by the ''Christliche Pfadfinderschaft Deutschlands'' in 1959 and bought in 1967. It is mainly used for training courses on national level, and the annual International Creative Workshop (IMWe). The VCP-Bundeszeltplatz was bought in 1997 and hosts camps from group to national level.\n\n== International Creative Workshop ==\nThe International Creative Workshop<ref name=\"IMWe Norway\">{{cite web |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190425144847/https://speiding.no/speiderprogram/speiderbasen/international-creative-workshop-imwe |url=https://speiding.no/speiderprogram/speiderbasen/international-creative-workshop-imwe |language=English, Norwegian |title=International Creative Workshop (IMWe) |date=28 March 2008 |first=Jostein |last=S\u00f8vik |archivedate=25 April 2019 |accessdate=25 April 2019 |url-status=live |website=[[Speiding.no]]}}</ref> ([[German language|German]]: ''Internationale Musische Werkstatt'' (IMWe))<ref name=\"eventsi\">{{cite web |url-status=live |title=IMWe 2018 - International Creative Workshop for Scouts |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190425144731/https://www.evensi.de/imwe-2018-international-creative-workshop-scouts-burg-rieneck-guide-scout-castle/208642623 |url=https://www.evensi.de/imwe-2018-international-creative-workshop-scouts-burg-rieneck-guide-scout-castle/208642623 |date=3 April 2018 |archivedate=25 April 2019 |accessdate=25 April 2019 |website=eventsi.de}}</ref> is an annual [[Scouting]] and [[Girl Guides|Guiding]] event run by the VCP.<ref name=\"Pfadi in Deutschland\">{{cite book |title=Die Pfadfinder in Deutschland 1909 - 2009 |trans-title=Scouting in Germany 1909 - 2009 |publisher=Novum Publishing |year=2011 |ISBN=978-3-99003-246-6 |first=Piet |last=Strunk |page=255 |language=German}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190425150605/https://www.der-kirchenkreis.de/de/aktuell/nachrichten/nachricht/article/bundesverdienstorden-fuer-bocholter-ehrenamt/ |date=12 October 2013 |url=https://www.der-kirchenkreis.de/de/aktuell/nachrichten/nachricht/article/bundesverdienstorden-fuer-bocholter-ehrenamt/ |title=Bundesverdienstorden f\u00fcr Bocholter Ehrenamt |trans-title=Federal Merit Order for Bocholt volunteer |url-status=live |language=German |archivedate=25 April 2019 |accessdate=25 April 2019 |publisher=[[Evangelical Church of Westphalia|Kirchenkreis Steinfurt-Coesfeld-Borken Evangelical Church]]}}</ref> It usually takes place at [[Rieneck Castle]].<ref name=\"IMWe Norway\"/> As a [[Wood Badge]] training event,<ref name=\"Pfadi in Deutschland\"/> the aim of IMWe is to give leaders of Guide and Scout groups the opportunity to explore their creative talents in a relaxed setting.<ref name=\"IMWe Norway\"/> IMWe is prepared on behalf of the VCP by an international group of scouts<ref name=\"IMWe Iceland\">{{cite web |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140720054132/http://skatamal.is/imwe |url=http://skatamal.is/imwe |website=[[skatamal.is]] |url-status=live |title=Vi\u00f0 beislum sk\u00f6punarkraftinn og n\u00fdtum \u00ed starfi\u00f0 |language=Icelandic |trans-title=We harness creativity and use it for the job |date=29 April 2014 |archivedate=20 July 2014 |accessdate=25 April 2019}}</ref> who meet several times a year to organize the workshop, which is held around [[Easter]].<ref name=\"IMWe Norway\"/> The workshop lasts for 8 or 9 days, with a [[Scout method#Symbolic framework|symbolic framework]] or theme.<ref name=\"IMWe Norway\"/> Participants have to be aged 17 years or older.<ref name=\"eventsi\"/><ref name=\"IMWe Norway\"/><ref>{{cite web |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190425144225/https://www.scout.ch/de/pfadialltag/internationales/lager/international-lager |url=https://www.scout.ch/de/pfadialltag/internationales/lager/international-lager |url-status=live |archivedate=25 April 2019 |accessdate=25 April 2019 |title=IMWE |website=[[Scout.ch]]}}</ref> IMWe has been represented at international Scouting events such as [[EuroJam 2005]]<ref>{{cite web |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160831151142/http://www.theblackmagic.de/54.html |url=http://www.theblackmagic.de/54.html |language=German |title=Buehne |trans-title=Stage |archivedate=31 August 2016 |publisher=[[Ring deutscher Pfadfinderverb\u00e4nde|German Contingent to the 2011 World Scout Jamboree]] |accessdate=25 April 2019}}</ref> and [[World Scout Moot]] in 2015.<ref name=\"IMWe Moot\">{{cite report |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180613185150/http://worldscoutmoot.is/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/Moot-Handbook-English.pdf |url-status=live |title=Moot Handbook |publisher=[[The Scout Association|UK Contingent to the 2017 World Scout Moot]] |archivedate=13 June 2018 |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180613185150/http://worldscoutmoot.is/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/Moot-Handbook-English.pdf#page=21 |page=21 |accessdate=25 April 2019}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Scouting in Germany]]\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Official website}}\n* [http://www.imwe.net IMWe homepage]\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Scouting and Guiding in Germany]]\n[[Category:World Association of Girl Guides and Girl Scouts member organizations]]\n[[Category:World Organization of the Scout Movement member organizations]]\n[[Category:Youth organizations established in 1973]]\n", "name_user": "Trappist the monk", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eProgram:remove 'invisible' characters from cs1|2 template parameters; (1\u00d7 NBSP)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Verband_Christlicher_Pfadfinderinnen_und_Pfadfinder"}
